docker-compose up -d --build
# If you encounter issues with Docker build cache, you can clear it using the following commands:
Clear the Docker builder cache:
docker builder prune --all
Optionally, clear unused images and containers:
docker system prune --all
Re-run your Docker build command, possibly with the --no-cache flag:
docker-compose build --no-cache

docker compose up -d --build portfolio-frontend


To backup a MongoDb database, you can use the following script. Make sure to replace the placeholders with your actual MongoDB connection details and desired backup location.

chmod +x backup-mongo.sh
./backup-mongo.sh